                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c5vDqTt",
                    "body": "```suggestion\r\nlemma toPerfectPairing_apply_apply_Polarization (x y : M) :\r\n```\r\nand maybe also worth adding:\r\n```lean\r\nlemma toPerfectPairing_apply_CoPolarization (x : N) :\r\n    P.toPerfectPairing (P.CoPolarization x) = P.CorootForm x := by\r\n  ext y\r\n  exact P.flip.toPerfectPairing_apply_apply_Polarization x y\r\n```\r\nfor symmetry.",
                    "createdAt": "2024-11-29T09:34:32Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "ocfnash"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "comments": {
                "nodes": [
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c5vD0QN",
                    "body": "How about:\r\n```suggestion\r\nlemma four_smul_rootForm_sq_eq_coxeterWeight_smul (i j : ι) :\r\n    4 • (P.RootForm (P.root i) (P.root j)) ^ 2 = P.coxeterWeight i j •\r\n      (P.RootForm (P.root i) (P.root i) * P.RootForm (P.root j) (P.root j)) := by\r\n```\r\nAdditionally, this result does not need ordered scalars and is not really connected with the nondegeneracy so I think it should be moved. I think a good home might be just below `rootForm_self_smul_coroot` in the `CanonicalBilinear.lean` file.",
                    "createdAt": "2024-11-29T10:02:30Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "ocfnash"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "comments": {
                "nodes": [
