                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c5vEa-5",
                    "body": "I suggest we first add the following lemma just below the definition of coxeterWeight:\r\n```lean\r\nlemma exists_int_eq_coxeterWeight (h : P.IsCrystallographic) (i j : ι) :\r\n    ∃ z : ℤ, P.coxeterWeight i j = z := by\r\n  obtain ⟨a, ha⟩ := P.isCrystallographic_iff.mp h i j\r\n  obtain ⟨b, hb⟩ := P.isCrystallographic_iff.mp h j i\r\n  exact ⟨a * b, by simp [coxeterWeight, ha, hb]⟩\r\n```\r\nand then use it as in the below (which also contains some other golfing / pruning):\r\n```suggestion\r\n  have hn0 : P.coxeterWeight i j ≠ 0 :=\r\n    fun hc ↦ hO <| (P.coxeterWeight_zero_iff_isOrthogonal P.RootForm i j).mp hc\r\n  have hn4 : P.coxeterWeight i j ≠ 4 := by\r\n    have : Module.IsReflexive R M := P.toPerfectPairing.reflexive_left\r\n    have : NoZeroSMulDivisors ℤ M := NoZeroSMulDivisors.int_of_charZero R M\r\n    intro hc\r\n    exact (P.infinite_of_linearly_independent_coxeterWeight_four i j h hc).not_finite inferInstance\r\n  have h4 : P.coxeterWeight i j ≤ 4 := P.coxeterWeight_le_4 i j\r\n  have : ∃ n : ℕ, P.coxeterWeight i j = n := by\r\n    obtain ⟨z, hz⟩ := P.exists_int_eq_coxeterWeight hP i j\r\n    have hz₀ : 0 ≤ z := by simpa [hz] using P.coxeterWeight_non_neg P.RootForm i j\r\n    obtain ⟨n, rfl⟩ := Int.eq_ofNat_of_zero_le hz₀\r\n    exact ⟨n, by simp [hz]⟩\r\n  obtain ⟨n, hcn⟩ := this\r\n```\r\nCould we also rename `infinite_of_linearly_independent_coxeterWeight_four` to `infinite_of_linearIndependent_coxeterWeight_four` while we're here?",
